      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DUBALENE (5) won a 58 first up and has threatened the two since over shorter sprints. Has been finishing off her races in good style, and the longer sprint should be right up her alley. PATRIOTICINTENTION (3) led them up and missed 1.6L by 1408m at Grafton. That followed a CL1 win at Port Macquarie. Has a low gate and a 3kg claim and can bounce back. PRINCE OF PROPHETS (1) settled a mile back in the same contest and caught the eye flashing home to be beaten just 1.8L. Had won a CL1 here by 6L prior on a heavy track, and he will be right in it with average luck. WHISKERS (6) led and bounced straight back into the winners' stall in a 58 at Taree over this distance. Stays down in the weights and is sure to give a bold sight.",
